  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd1 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db9\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't give, the child is sacrificed to the crocodile",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sigiriya Police say that a 7-year-old child who was swimming in the Dambulla Kandalama Kumbukkadanwala Lake with his mother and father was grabbed by a crocodile.",
        "The police say that the police have carried out operations together with lifeguards and village personnel to find the child who was grabbed by the crocodile.",
        "Thus, a small child named Chanut Satsara, who studied in the second year of DS Senanayake Vidyalaya, Dambulla Kandalama, a resident of Kumbukkadanwala area, has been grabbed by the crocodile.",
        "The child's father mentioned that because there are crocodiles in this lake, many people do not bathe. For many days, all the family came to bathe in this lake for the first time to fulfill the child's desire because of the mentions that their son needed to bathe in this lake."
      ],
